## Project Overview

The Movie App allows users to log in using their credentials and browse through a collection of movies. The app implements `next-auth` for authentication, a search bar for filtering movies, and a UI grid to display movie details.

## Features

- User Authentication using `next-auth` with credentials provider.
- Movie search functionality.
- Responsive design using Material UI components.
- Dynamic filtering of movies based on the search query.
- Protected routes for authenticated users.

## Technologies Used

- [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) - Framework for server-rendered React apps.
- [next-auth](https://next-auth.js.org/) - Authentication for Next.js.
- [Material UI (MUI)](https://mui.com/) - UI library for React.
- [React Hook Form](https://react-hook-form.com/) - Form handling.
- [Yup](https://github.com/jquense/yup) - Validation schema.
- [Toaster](https://react-hot-toast.com/) - Toast notifications.

